================================================================================
CO2 BIKE CALCULATOR API - SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
================================================================================

PROJECT: CO2 Bike Calculator using MEVO (Polish bike sharing)
LANGUAGE: Python 3
FRAMEWORK: Flask

================================================================================
WHAT YOU HAVE:
================================================================================

CORE FILES:
  - app.py              Main Flask API application
  - providers.py        MEVO provider integration (GBFS)
  - index.html          Frontend interface
  - requirements.txt    Python dependencies
  - start.py            Start script with tests
  - start.sh            Bash version of start script
  - test.log            Last test results

OPTIONAL CLEANUP:
  - cleanup_final.sh    Remove all .md and unnecessary files

================================================================================
HOW TO RUN:
================================================================================

1. Install dependencies (first time only):
   pip install -r requirements.txt

2. Start API with tests:
   python3 start.py

OR just start server:
   python3 app.py

The API will be available at: http://localhost:3000

================================================================================
API ENDPOINTS:
================================================================================

GET /health
  - Health check endpoint
  - Returns: {"status":"OK","provider":"MEVO"}

GET /v1/nearby-stations
  - Get nearby MEVO bike stations
  - Query params: latitude, longitude, radius (optional, default 1.0)
  - Example: http://localhost:3000/v1/nearby-stations?latitude=54.3520&longitude=18.6466&radius=2

POST /v1/calculate-co2-savings
  - Calculate CO2 savings for a bike trip vs car
  - Body: {"latitude":54.3520,"longitude":18.6466,"destination_latitude":54.4000,"destination_longitude":18.7000}
  - Returns: distance, co2_savings_kg, travel_times, environmental_impact, closest_bike

GET /
  - Serves index.html frontend

================================================================================
WHAT IT DOES:
================================================================================

1. Fetches real-time bike availability from MEVO API (GBFS standard)
2. Finds closest available bikes to user location
3. Calculates CO2 savings when choosing bike over car
4. Shows travel time comparison (bike vs car)
5. Displays environmental impact (CO2 in grams, equivalent trees saved)

================================================================================
DATA SOURCES:
================================================================================

MEVO (Polish Bike Sharing):
  - Base URL: https://gbfs.urbansharing.com/rowermevo.pl
  - Endpoints: station_information.json, station_status.json
  - Header required: Client-Identifier

================================================================================
ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:
================================================================================

PORT (optional, default 3000):
  - Set port for API server
  - Example: PORT=8000 python3 app.py

DEBUG (optional, default False):
  - Enable Flask debug mode
  - Example: DEBUG=True python3 app.py

================================================================================
TESTING:
================================================================================

Run start.py to automatically:
  1. Install dependencies
  2. Start Flask server
  3. Run API tests
  4. Log results to test.log

Check test.log to see test results and API responses.

================================================================================
CLEANUP:
================================================================================

To remove all unnecessary .md files and Go files:
  chmod +x cleanup_final.sh
  ./cleanup_final.sh

This will keep only the API essentials.

